Race.SpecificTitle: Justice of the Peace -- Justice of the Peace & Constable District 3
North Sabine Fire Protection District -- 5 Mills - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText: North Sabine Fire Protection District Proposition
Race.FullText: Shall North Sabine Fire Protection District, Parish of Sabine, State of Louisiana ("the District"), pursuant to Article VI, Section 19 of the Louisiana Constitution of 1974, Part I of Chapter 7 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950, as amended (La. R.S. 40:1501), and other constitutional and statutory authority, be authorized to renew the levy and collection of an ad valorem tax of 5.00 mills (the "Tax") (an estimated $500,000 is reasonably expected to be collected from the levy of the Tax for the entire first year, and this amount will increase if the value of property subject to taxation increases) in each calendar year on all property subject to taxation in the Fire District for a period of 10 years, commencing in the year 2015 to and including the year 2024, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, maintaining, manning and operating fire protection facilities and equipment in and for the District and paying the costs of obtaining water for fire protection purposes?
